! Familiar

//An AI familiar for your wiki.// Familiar adds streaming AI chat, note summaries, tag and task suggestions, and related-note discovery to ''any'' ~TiddlyWiki — powered by the self-hosted [[Familiar gateway|https://github.com/mblackman/tiddly-familiar]], so your notes never leave your own infrastructure.

!! Configuration

Open //Control Panel → Settings → Familiar// (or edit the tiddlers below directly). Changes apply to the next request — no reload needed.

|!Tiddler |!Purpose |!Default |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/GatewayURL` |Gateway base URL |`http://localhost:8787` |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/APIKey` |`GATEWAY_API_KEY` from your `.env` |(empty) |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/ChatNoteTemplate` |Title template for ''New note'' chats — tokens: `{name}` (random adjective-noun), `{date}` (YYYY-MM-DD), `{time}` (HH:MM) |`AI Chat: {name}` |

!!! Advanced — retrieval tuning

Optional per-request overrides (Control Panel → Settings → Familiar). Leave a tiddler ''blank'' to use the gateway's own setting; changes apply to the next request.

|!Tiddler |!Purpose |!Blank = |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/RagTopK` |Top-ranked notes fed to each answer (gateway `RAG_TOP_K`) |server default (8) |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/QueryRewrite` |Rewrite chat follow-ups into a standalone search query before retrieving (`yes`/`no`) |server default (`RAG_QUERY_REWRITE`) |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/MaxTiddlers` |Notes embedded per request — the cache-miss ceiling, not the candidate pool (gateway `max_tiddlers`) |server default (100) |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/SearchResultCount` |Results returned by sidebar semantic search |10 |
|`$:/config/mblackman/familiar/RelatedCount` |Related notes suggested per note |5 |

Upgrading from the pre-rename //AI Gateway// plugin? Your settings are migrated automatically on first startup — just uninstall the old `$:/plugins/mblackman/ai-gateway` plugin.

!! How it works

This wiki sends its own note content with each request, so every feature works against ''any'' ~TiddlyWiki — the gateway needs no configuration or credentials for it. Payloads are minimized through the gateway's content-addressed note cache: each note is hashed (sha256), the gateway is asked which hashes it is missing, and only those travel in full — unchanged notes cost a few bytes per question. ''Summarize'', ''Suggest tags'' and ''Extract tasks'' render the note to plain text in the browser and send that.

Limits (matching the gateway's): at most 500 notes per question, 50k characters per note, 2M characters total — overflow is dropped and the answer is annotated with how many notes were searched (narrow the filter to control which).

!! Features

* ''Ask your familiar'' — sidebar panel with a question field and optional ~TiddlyWiki filter; renders the answer with a collapsible source list.
* ''Saved chats'' — ''Save chat'' turns the sidebar conversation into a regular note tagged `ai-chat` (one tiddler per turn under `<note>/turn/`), so it syncs and survives reload. While saved, new turns keep landing in the note; ''Continue this chat'' on the note re-binds the sidebar to it later. ''New chat'' starts fresh without touching saved notes.
* ''New note'' — creates a chat note ''up front'' so the conversation persists from the first turn. The title is proposed from the `ChatNoteTemplate` config tiddler; edit it in place or tap the dice to roll another name, then ''Create'' opens the note and binds the panel to it.
* ''new AI chat'' page-control button (next to ''new tiddler'') — one tap creates a chat note with a freshly generated template title, opens it, and binds the panel to it. Hide or reorder it under //Control Panel → Appearance → Toolbars → Page Toolbar//.
* ''In-note chat'' — every `ai-chat` note renders its transcript with a composer underneath, so you can keep asking right in the tiddler and the conversation records itself there. Tag ''any'' note `ai-chat` to start an embedded chat from scratch.
* ''Summarize'' — toolbar button on any tiddler; calls the gateway with the tiddler as context and writes the result to a `summary` field, shown in the ''Familiar'' info-dropdown tab.
* ''Familiar info tab'' — the tiddler info dropdown (ⓘ) gains a ''Familiar'' tab that gathers the note's derived data on demand: ''AI Summary'', ''Related notes'', ''Suggested tags'' and ''Tasks''. Nothing is rendered on the note until you open the tab and ask for it, so notes stay clean.
* ''Insert into note'' — Summary and Tasks each offer an ''Insert into note'' button that writes the result into the note body as editable ~TiddlyWiki (or Markdown, matching the note's type): the summary as a quote block at the top, the tasks as a list at the end. Tag suggestions apply straight to the note's real `tags`.
